ternal links from june engvarb from august use dmy dates from august all articles with unsourced statementsarticles with unsourced statements from september articles with specifically marked weaselworded phrases from july  navigation menu personal tools not logged intalkcontributionscreate accountlog in namespaces article talk variants views read edit view history more search navigation main pagecontentsfeatured contentcurrent eventsrandom articledonate to wikipediawikipedia store interaction helpabout wikipediacommunity portalrecent changescontact page tools what links hererelated changesupload filespecial pagespermanent linkpage informationwikidata itemcite this page printexport create a bookdownload as pdfprintable version in other projects wikimedia commons languages deutschbahasa melayu edit links this page was last edited on  july  at  text is available under the creative commons attributionsharealike license additional terms may apply by using this site you agree to the terms of use and privacy policy wikipedia® is a registered trademark of the wikimedia foundation inc a nonprofit organization privacy policy about wikipedia disclaimers contact wikipedia developers cookie statement mobile view waheed alli baron alli  wikipedia waheed alli baron alli from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search the lord alli chancellor of de montfort university in office – vicechancellor philip tasker dominic shellard preceded by the baroness prashar succeeded by the baroness lawrence member of the house of lords lord temporal incumbent assumed office  july  life peerage personal details born waheed alli   november  age  croydon london uk nationality british political party labour profession media entrepreneur waheed alli baron alli born  november  is a british multimillionaire media entrepreneur and politician he was cofounder and managing director of planet  a tv production company and managing director at carlton television productions he was until november  chairman of asoscom he is the chief executive of silvergate media which purchased two of the media rights previously held by chorion ltd where alli was former chairman he is a labour life peer and is described as one of only a few openly gay muslim politicians in the world contents  biography  business career  politics  other information  awards and nominations  references  external links biographyedit in british political terms he is considered asian though both of his parents are from the caribbean see indocaribbean his mother a nurse is from trinidad and his estranged father a mechanic is from british guiana now guyana his mother was hindu and his father muslim he has two brothers who are also muslims he was named one of the  most important asians in british media in  at the same time he maintains ties with his caribbean roots both with other britishguyanese politicians such as valerie amos and trevor phillips and with president bharrat jagdeo he is one of a group of highly successful guyanese people in britain michael white of the guardian refers to them as the guyanese mafia which includes raj persaud herman ouseley and david dabydeen cynthia pine keith waithe and rudolph dunbar alli grew up in humble surroundings attended stanley technical college in south norwood and left school at  with nine olevels business careeredit alli started work as a junior researcher for a finance magazine crediting his first success to salem ghayar who hired and mentored him after a few years of preparing monthly reports for potential investors he was headhunted by save  prosper part of robert fleming  co eventually he returned to his original employer and worked his way up in the media business within robert maxwells stable of publications he then went to the city for a second career in investment banking through which he became wealthy in the mids he met charlie parsons who was to become his business partner as well as his life partner allis third career and the first in which he achieved public prominence was in the television industry he and parsons set up  hour productions which produced the word the most talked about television programme in britain in  they merged with bob geldofs planet pictures to form planet  such was its success that it became one of the largest tv production companies in the country and the main independent supplier to channel  it was responsible for genrebreaking programmes such as big breakfast and survivor carlton television bought planet  in march  for £ million with alli and parsons prudently retaining the rights to the lucrative survivor format waheed alli became a carlton board director before stepping down a year later in april  alli took over as chairman of the media rights company chorion ltd which owns rights to enid blyton and agatha christie and has offices beyond the uk in new york sydney and tokyo he was chairman of aimlisted asoscom and a director of olga television entertainer paul ogradys production company he owns part of shine limited a media production company he cofounded in march  with elisabeth murdoch daughter of mediamagnate rupert murdoch in august  he stepped down from the chairmanship of chorion and sold half his stake in asoscom to start a new company called silvergate mediacitation needed he was part of a failed £m bid backed by private equity firm i to buy virgin radio from smg plc in  in march  he was appointed as smgs nonexecutive director alli is a founder investor in koovs an indian online retailer looking to replicate the success of asos in the subcontinent the company was set up in  and intends to raise £m with a stock market listing on londons aim politicsedit alli joined the labour party at the persuasion of his neighbour emily thornberry to whom he remains close he is also close to anji hunter director of government relations in tony blairs first government prime minister blair used him for years as a means to help him reach out to a younger generation aka yoof culture and as such he is consideredby whom one of tonys cronies he was made a life peer as baron alli of norbury in the london borough of croydon on  july  at the age of  becoming the youngest and the first openlygay peer in parliament he sits on the labour benches in the house of lords the bbc summarised his appointment as the antithesis of the stereotypical establishment peer – young asian and from the world of media and entertainment alli has used his political position to argue for gay rights he spearheaded the campaign to repeal section  he advocated lowering the age of consent for homosexuals from  to  equal to heterosexuals this eventually became law as the sexual offences amendment act  it was during a heated exchange with conservative opponents led by baroness young that he informed his fellow peers that he was gay in april  he said in a speech i have never been confused about my sexuality i have been confused about the way i am treated as a result of it the only confusion lies in the prejudice shown some of it tonight ie in the house and much of it enshrined in the law in  he participated the international conference on lgbt human rights adopting declaration of montreal and in  he spearheaded an effort to repeal clauses in the civil partnership act  which prohibited religious institutions from conducting the ceremonies on their premises this campaign culminated in a bipartisan amendment which became part of the equality act  he influenced the draft communications bill in  other informationedit allis work has been focused around gay rights youth and education he is the former chancellor of de montfort university in leicester he is also the president of the croydon youth development trust he is a patron of skillset the sector skills council supporting skills and training within the creative media industries in autumn  he won a stonewall award for the category of political figure in  he became a patron of the albert kennedy trust stating being a teenager isnt easy and its particularly difficult for vulnerable and socially excluded members of our community the albert kennedy trust offers young gay men lesbians and bisexuals a unique and targeted service my first task as patron will be to support plans to extend these services across the uk to help the increasing number of young people contacting the trust he was a keynote speaker at the international conference on lgbt human rights part of the  world outgames which led to the declaration of montreal alli is a patron of oxford pride the annual pride event in oxfordshire and of pride london he is a patron of the elton john aids foundation a portrait of alli is in the national portrait gallery collection which contains portraits of the nations great men and women awards and nominationsedit year association category nominees result  diversity in media awards diversity champion of the year lord waheed alli nominated referencesedit  edgecliffejohnson andrew lunch with the ft waheed alli ft retrieved  february  one of the few gay muslims in british public life   alderson andrew  march  lord alli attacks bishops in gay marriage row telegraph retrieved  april  one of the few openlygay muslim politicians   vasagar jeevan kelso paul jamesgregory sally dodd vikram  june  profiles of  leading british muslims london the guardian retrieved  april    a b c most powerful asians in british media lord waheed alli asians in media  a b john muir caribbean peers caribbean voice october   michael white balls gets his retaliation in first as annual gcse row begins the guardian  august   guyanese achievers uk  by dindayal vidur  a b c knitting circle  interviewed by shahid the asian outlook no date approximately   a b c d profile lord waheed alli bbc news online  november  retrieved  may    the party boys the independent saturday  june    vasagar jeevan kelso paul jamesgregory sally dodd vikram  june  profiles of  leading british muslims london the guardian retrieved  may    hands off noddy the daily tele